In July 2019, Trump tweeted that four Democratic members of Congress – all four minority women, three of them native-born Americans – should "go back" to the countries they "came from".[910] Two days later the House of Representatives voted 240–187, mostly along party lines, to condemn his "racist comments".[911] White nationalist publications and social media sites praised his remarks, which continued over the following days.[912] Trump continued to make similar remarks during his 2020 campaign.[913]
